le without implying they are editable yet.\n\nSTAGE SCAFFOLD\n\nWrite the story in segments\n\nComposition will become the durable writing surface, with live progress, resumable segments, and room for mid-stream direction changes.\n\nIn progress\nUnlocked\n\nThe route and the durable session stage are aligned. Live editors and job views can mount here later without changing the URL pattern.\n\nCOMPOSITION RUNTIME\n\nStory draft complete\n\nLive updates are connected. The manuscript is showing the latest saved checkpoint.\n\n100%\nOverall draft\nWriting progress\n100% complete\n\n249 words drafted so far against a soft target of about 1600.\n\nCurrent focus\n\nChapter 3: All Is Lost to Finale\n\nMove through the brief low point and guide the harbor back into rest.\n\nRecent recap\n\nLatest segment summary\n\nRewrite segment 3 leaves Mira calmer, keeps the bell promise active, and sends Pip forward as visible support.\n\nDrafted so far\n\n249 words\n\nBeat focus: All Is Lost \u00b7 Finale.\n\nREWRITE REVIEW\n\nChapter 3: All Is Lost to Finale\n\nCompare the proposed rewrite against the current manuscript before accepting it.\n\ncompleted\nPending review\nSaved checkpoint\nSegment 3 of 2\nAll Is Lost\nFinale\nRewrite segment 3 leaves Mira calmer, keeps the bell promise active, and sends Pip forward as visible support.\nRewrite segment 3 lets Mira follow the silver bell through a gentle stretch of harbor water while the night stays readable, warm, and unmistakably safe for bedtime listening.\n\nPip stays close enough to steady every surprise, and the prose keeps the movement soft, patient, visibly cared for, and easy for a sleepy child to trust.\n\nThe moment lands in calm repair, so Mira and Pip can rest before the next handoff, with the harbor settled, the promise intact, and the final image quiet.\nWriting controls\n\nPause, resume, rewrite earlier passages, or step back to the plan without losing the durable checkpoint.\n\nPending rewrite\n\nReview segments 2 to 3\n